response_text: The official pricing information for Runkeeper does not seem to be accessible directly via a dedicated page. However, subscription details for Runkeeper Go are generally offered through their app or website. You might explore their offerings via the main page [Runkeeper](https://runkeeper.com) or reach out directly for accurate details. #### Your Privacy

This site uses cookies and similar tracking tools, some of which are provided by third parties, to operate, protect and improve our site, enable social media and other features, support our advertising and marketing efforts, and give you the best possible experience. These cookies and tools may enable us and these third parties to collect user data and communications, IP address and online identifiers, referring URLs and other content and browsing information, and record user sessions and interactions with this site. You can opt-out of most cookies on our site, other than those that are Necessary and Functional. However, even if you opt out, our site will still serve Functional and Necessary cookies (e.g., those we use to optimize site performance and page or content loading, manage and distribute traffic, secure the site and our services, and detect and prevent fraud and malicious activity), which may enable us and third parties to collect and track certain user data, such as IP address, device ID and other online identifiers, referring URLs, browser and OS type and version, date/time stamps, and other browsing data. Further, opting out of certain cookies may impact your experiences and the performance of the site.  
  
Click on the different cookie category headings to find out more about the categories of cookies we and third parties use and change your browser preferences for them on our site, as applicable. More Info: [Privacy Policy](https://www.asics.com/us/en-us/privacy-policy.html) and [Cookie Policy.](https://www.asics.com/us/en-us/cookie-policy.html)

**Opt Out of Targeted Advertising**: Our site includes Targeting, Marketing & Social Media cookies, some of which enable us and third parties to collect and use user data and browsing information about you in order to reach you with targeted advertising. You can find more information about the use of these Targeting, Marketing & Social Media cookies on our site and opt your browser out of these cookies on our site, by clicking the “Targeting, Marketing & Social Media” tab to the left and turning off these cookies. You may also submit a request to opt out of targeted advertising via our Consumer Rights Request page [here.](https://privacyportal-de.onetrust.com/webform/d516dd52-7883-4a41-851f-6c02e52beca9/6d6dd848-b5f9-4d27-8eba-d9216af92097) (Note: submitting a request on this page will not opt your browser out of sales and sharing (i.e., via cookies) on our site).

Please note that your preferences are browser specific. So, if you come to our site from a different browser or device, you will need to set your preferences for that browser and device as well.

#### Functional & Necessary

Always Active

We use Functional and Necessary cookies to ensure that the sites and services function properly and securely, to prevent fraud and misuse, and to enable certain functionality. Some of these cookies are necessary to the ongoing operation of the sites and services, meaning a site will not function properly or at all without them. For example, some Necessary and Functional cookies are used for load balancing and traffic distribution/routing and to optimize page and content loading on our Sites. Functional and Necessary cookies also include cookies that enable us to secure the sites and services (e.g., to detect and block bot activity and other malicious traffic, prevent Denial of Service (DDOS) attacks, detect bugs and errors, and securely process transactions), as well as cookies that we use to detect and prevent fraud and misuse (e.g., to detect and block suspicious logins and fraudulent transactions). In addition, some Necessary and Functional cookies enable certain key site functionality (e.g., account logins, adding items to your shopping cart, submitting webforms, and checking out with Apple Pay, PayPal, and other third party payment services).

Given the important role these cookies play, these cookies are set to “always active” on our site, which means that you cannot “opt out” of or turn them off using this privacy preference manager. You may be able to block or delete Functional and Necessary cookies through your browser setting, but if you do so certain features and content may be unavailable or non-operational. [More Info](https://www.asics.com/us/en-us/cookie-policy.html).

#### Performance & Analytics

 Performance & Analytics

Performance and Analytics cookies allow us to collect, measure and analyze audience, activity and usage information about the sites and services, so we can evaluate and improve the performance of our sites and services. For example, Performance and Analytics cookies may provide us with insights on which pages are the most and least popular and which pages are the most and least popular and how users move around our sites and services. They also allow us to remember preferences and settings you have selected and help us identify issues users face on our sites and services. [More Info](https://www.asics.com/us/en-us/cookie-policy.html).

#### Targeting, Marketing & Social Media

 Targeting, Marketing & Social Media

Targeting, Marketing and Social Media cookies may be set by us or by third party ad companies and social media networks. These cookies allow us and third parties to make your user experience more personal, reach you with more relevant ads, and measure and improve ad campaigns. These third parties may also combine the information about you that they collect through our site, with information that they collect about you (including browsing, search history, usage data, content and activity information) from third party sites, services and sources, which they may use to build a profile of your interests, show you relevant advertising on our sites and across third party sites and services, and measure and improve ad campaigns and services.

Targeting, Marketing, & Social Media cookies also include cookies that enable social media and other features on our sites and services, including the possibility to connect you to your social networks (e.g., Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, TikTok, X and LinkedIn) and share content from our sites or services through social media. If you do not allow Targeting, Marketing and Social Media cookies, you will still receive ads from us but they will be less relevant and tailored to your interests, and certain social media features will not be available within our site.
